title._content: New Concord, Ohio, Girl Scout Troups 187 and 506 Honored with 2005 Take Pride in America Award, 09/29/2005

description._content: Original Caption: Take Pride in America Director Martha Allbright, fourth from left, and Secretary Gale Norton, fifth from left, with members of Girl Scout Troop 187 and 506 from New Concord, Ohio, honored with 2005 Take Pride in America Award for wetlands, nature trail, other projects enhancing Camp Falls Run in northwestern Appalachia, 09/29/2005 U.S. National Archives’ Local Identifier: 48-DP-Norton Fall 05 reprints From: Series: Photographs Documenting the Secretary's Activities, and Agency Officials, Events, Programs, and Managed Sites, compiled 2001 - 2006 Created By: Department of the Interior.
